        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-09-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="716"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                <head>716. Telegram 295 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d716fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/9–2156. Confidential;
                        Priority; Limit Distribution.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-09-21"
                            >September 21, 1956, 6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d716-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d716-1"/>
                <p>295. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Am making no press comment on CHICOM statement (my telegram 293). If Department
                    issues reply would appreciate prompt transmittal here.</p>
                <p>At tomorrow’s meeting plan ignore CHICOM’s statement unless raised by him and
                    proceed along lines Deptel 301.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Popper</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
